	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>March 27&#47;57</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dr Sir&#47;</p>
				<p>I may as well send you<lb/> the few Dollars I have in hand.<lb/>  I have been paid.</p>
				<p><persName>Jonas N. Phillips</persName> 3.00<lb/> <persName>M. Morrison</persName> 3.00 <persName>Dittenhoeffer</persName> <hi rend="sup">1.50</hi>&#47;<hi rend="sub">100</hi><lb/> <persName>Mr H. Levy</persName> <hi rend="sup">1.50</hi>&#47;<hi rend="sub">100</hi> &#38; <persName>Hy. Simons</persName> 6.00 making<lb/> in all 15.00 now I have to deduct<lb/> for last month carriage for parcel <hi rend="sup">62</hi>&#47;<hi rend="sub">100</hi><lb/> for Delivery 2100&#8212;this month <hi rend="sup">25</hi>&#47;<hi rend="sub">100</hi><lb/> <hi rend="sup">1.88</hi>&#47;<hi rend="sub">100</hi> total 4.75 laid out<lb/> take off for the 10&#47; on 33.00 sent last time<lb/> without charge of <add>&#63;</add> on 16.00<lb/> this time 4.80. total taken off <hi rend="sup">4.75 &#38; 4.80</hi>&#47;<hi rend="sub">9.55</hi>.<lb/> 9.55 off 15.00 there remain 5.45 add to it<lb/> 10.50 for Bible &#38; Prayer Book 10.50 it makes<lb/> in all 15.95.  I have here to observe that <persName>Mr. H. Levy</persName> has ceased to take your<lb/> Publication also <persName>Soln Weil</persName> &#38; <persName>Miss<lb/> Sarah Cohen</persName>&#44; for the last I am sorry<lb/> for I think it is pressure of circumstances</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>makes her discontinue it.</p>
				<p><persName>Abm Stein</persName> also not only will not take<lb/> it but will not pay&#8212;he says when<lb/> he last paid you he told you not<lb/> to send it again&#44; for he never reads it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">After calling a number of times<lb/> on <persName>Ritterband</persName> he <sic>shewd</sic> me at last<lb/> your Receipts for 12.00 paid in <date>May 55</date><lb/> up to <date>March 1855</date> &#38; yet I hold Bills<lb/> against him for 12.00 while he only owes<lb/> 3.00 part of the last Bill for 2 years<lb/> I am often made to look very foolish<lb/> when so many dispute their accounts<lb/> &#38; in cases they are right.  I look<lb/> anxiously for the time when you<lb/> may be here yourself to see to the<lb/> matter&#44; as so many have refused to<lb/> continue taking your paper.<lb/>  I really do not know what to<lb/> make of it&#8212;what has come over<lb/> the people.  Do send the parcel in<lb/> time next week that the man<lb/> have time to give them out.<lb/>  The last was not delivered till<lb/> <date>Saturday&#44; the 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> last &#38; therefore<lb/> the man did not deliver them</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>some days afterwards</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I remain Dr Sir yours very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">M. Rubenstein</persName></p>
				<p>Send in the parcel one<lb/> of your Bibles&#44; such a one<lb/> as you sent me last&#44;<lb/> but you informed me that<lb/> it was the last&#44; &#38; I cannot<lb/> get one of <persName>Mr Isaacs</persName> except<lb/> a 12 Dollar one&#44; so if you<lb/> can one bound for me in time<lb/> send it&#44; I mean the 8 Dollar one</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M.R.</persName></p>
		</body>
